  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n      \t\t\t\t\t\u003cul\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cli id=\"Entry1\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca name=\"entry\" id=\"EntryAnchor\"\u003eanchor\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/13/13c3b37e26087d674df8ff3cc048cbed.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\" title=\"Image: Shuaizhi Tian/Pexels\" data-size=\"3024x4032\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cimg srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/13/13c3b37e26087d674df8ff3cc048cbed.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/13/13c3b37e26087d674df8ff3cc048cbed.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/13/13c3b37e26087d674df8ff3cc048cbed.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\" src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/13/13c3b37e26087d674df8ff3cc048cbed.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" title=\"Image: Shuaizhi Tian/Pexels\" alt=\"Image: Shuaizhi Tian/Pexels\" width=\"514\" height=\"\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eImage: Shuaizhi Tian/Pexels\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t        \t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/tag/2448959/construction-input-prices\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eConstruction input prices\u003c/a\u003e decreased by 0.2% for the month of December, according to a new \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/tag/2138957/associated-builders-and-contractors/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAssociated Builders and Contractors\u003c/a\u003e (ABC) analysis of U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics Producer Price Index data. Nonresidential construction input prices decreased 0.2% for the month, and overall construction input prices are 0.9% higher than a year ago.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDecember’s nonresidential construction input prices are now also 0.6% higher. Prices for steel mill products (-3.0%) and iron and steel (-2.5%) dropped while the price of softwood lumber (1.1%) and hot rolled steel bars, plates, and structural shapes (2.5%) increased.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/ca/ca642e77bfa3d3deb141a2f9e184fac3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x560\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/ca/ca642e77bfa3d3deb141a2f9e184fac3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/ca/ca642e77bfa3d3deb141a2f9e184fac3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/ca/ca642e77bfa3d3deb141a2f9e184fac3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/ca/ca642e77bfa3d3deb141a2f9e184fac3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eChart credit: Associated Builders and Contractors\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e“Construction materials prices declined slightly in December and are virtually unchanged over the past two years,” ABC Chief Economist Anirban Basu said. “Of course, there is significant variability across input categories. Much of the recent moderation can be tracked to lower energy prices; diesel prices, for instance, are down roughly $0.45/gallon since December 2023.\u0026#34;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/16/16d161130d8bd4ac99807815ea201f91.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x898\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/16/16d161130d8bd4ac99807815ea201f91.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/16/16d161130d8bd4ac99807815ea201f91.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/16/16d161130d8bd4ac99807815ea201f91.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/16/16d161130d8bd4ac99807815ea201f91.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eChart credit: Associated Builders and Contractors\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026#34;Prices for other inputs, like copper wire and cable or sand and gravel products, have escalated significantly over the past year. For the industry, however, the fact that overall input prices have remained flat in recent quarters is purely good news. Just 20% of contractors expect their profit margins to decline over the next six months, according to ABC’s Construction Confidence Index,\u0026#34; his statement continued.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBasu\u0026#39;s predictions for the year ahead were recently included in our \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/features/article/150458787/architecture-community-2025-predictions-adaptive-reuse-housing-failures-diversity-efforts-interest-rates-discovery-of-the-imperfect-and-much-more\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eArchitecture Community 2025 Predictions\u003c/a\u003e feature. The ABC analysis of November\u0026#39;s construction input price data can also be found \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/article/150457480/november-s-construction-input-prices-remain-flat\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ehere\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cbr clear=\"all\"/\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\u003ch2\u003eSimilar articles on Archinect that may interest you...\u003c/h2\u003e\n\t\t\u003cul\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/article/150322028/construction-costs-projected-to-see-largest-increase-in-years-due-to-supply-and-demand-pressures\" title=\"Construction costs projected to see largest increase in years due to supply and demand pressures\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cimg srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/23/23a3200742ae0286651fb8bd213c9fb1.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=248\u0026amp;h=147 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/23/23a3200742ae0286651fb8bd213c9fb1.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=248\u0026amp;h=147\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/23/23a3200742ae0286651fb8bd213c9fb1.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=248\u0026amp;h=147\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\" src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/23/23a3200742ae0286651fb8bd213c9fb1.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=248\u0026amp;h=147\" title=\"Construction costs projected to see largest increase in years due to supply and demand pressures\" alt=\"Construction costs projected to see largest increase in years due to supply and demand pressures\" width=\"248\" height=\"147\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eConstruction costs projected to see largest increase in years due to supply and demand pressures\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/a\u